The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in England so far as at 19 October is 629,211 (1,117.9 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 15 October, there were 93,497 new confirmed cases (166.1 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 08 October, there were 89,723 new cases and so the new cases have risen by 4% ( 3,774 extra cases).
